AUDIO: 'Today we\'re looking at a tool that automates [music] the process of generating your sound effects and music tracks for your videos, but is it any good? Let\'s find out. Welcome back to the channel where we discuss the creative uses of AI and I have been waiting for a tool like this'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for so long. There have been people who have tried it, but I think this is the best implementation and it\'s coming from Ace Studio, a program that I featured many times on this channel and I recommend that you go check out at least one or two of these videos. It is truly'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a revolutionary approach to creating AI music and at its core, it converts MIDI data into voices that you can customize and add lyrics to and it actually has many of the same features that you\'ll find in something like Suno Studio. But today we\'re talking about their video'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'export feature, which applies music and sound effects to a video that you bring into it after it analyzes and decides where things should go. But of course, you don\'t have to just go with what they give you. You can use it as a starting'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'point and go from there. And the best part about it is its basic functionality is super easy to implement and understand. Again, I\'ll ask you to watch a previous video to get up to speed on what Ace Studio is about and how it works, but this is what you are met with when you first start the program. It\'s'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'basically an empty grid and to use the video export feature, you first drag in a video. Today I\'ve created a few video clips that were generated with sound and music on their own, but we\'re going to take all of that out and let Ace Studio create all of that sound from scratch. These videos were chosen because they'

[01:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lend themselves to adding sound effects and creating very specific emotional musical mood. So I\'m just going to start with this one. I\'m actually going to turn down the audio completely of the original and just let you take a look at what the video looks like. It\'s a tornado coming in from the distance. We'

[01:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a farmhouse here. We have farm animals. We have horses and cows and the idea is that this tornado is going to come in and destroy the house because that\'s what tornadoes do, isn\'t it? Once the video is imported, you begin your'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conversation with the agent and the agent will allow you to converse your way through exactly what you want. Starting at the very basic level, creating either music for the video or sound effects for the video. Now with my experimentation, I find that I like to'

